WEBVTT

00:10.594 --> 00:11.929
♪ You could do it solo ♪

00:11.929 --> 00:13.931
♪ But then you'd be all by yourself ♪

00:13.931 --> 00:16.433
♪ Yo! So, it'd be more fun
To share this one ♪

00:16.433 --> 00:17.935
♪ With someone else ♪

00:17.935 --> 00:21.772
♪ Together we will soar
Across the sky and beyond ♪

00:21.772 --> 00:23.273
♪ So turn up your voice ♪

00:23.899 --> 00:25.651
♪ Stand up and sing along ♪

00:25.651 --> 00:27.611
♪ All different voices
Everybody now! ♪

00:27.611 --> 00:29.446
♪ Our melodies ringing ♪

00:29.446 --> 00:31.156
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:31.323 --> 00:33.325
♪ Yeah, we're livin' in harmony ♪

00:33.325 --> 00:35.285
♪ Our song is much stronger ♪

00:35.285 --> 00:37.120
♪ With every troll singing ♪

00:37.120 --> 00:39.915
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪♪

00:43.460 --> 00:46.463
[ Lownote humming ]

00:46.463 --> 00:47.589
‐ Oh, yeah.

00:47.589 --> 00:49.299
[ Lownote humming ]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.343
‐ Whoa‐ho‐ho, Lownote,

00:51.343 --> 00:54.096
looks like someone's got
a little extra grove

00:54.096 --> 00:55.555
in their step today?

00:55.555 --> 00:57.808
And why, pray tell, is that?

00:58.267 --> 01:02.312
‐ Well, since you asked,
it's 'cuz today is my birthday.

01:02.312 --> 01:04.940
But, given that you're the Troll
who makes a big deal

01:04.940 --> 01:07.150
out of every Trolls‐Topian's birthday,

01:07.693 --> 01:10.487
I think you know that already.

01:11.863 --> 01:14.241
‐ Oh, you know I do!

01:15.826 --> 01:17.953
[ Lownote and Poppy laughing ]

01:18.954 --> 01:19.871
[ Poppy screaming ]

01:19.871 --> 01:21.790
I had no idea it was his birthday!

01:21.790 --> 01:23.208
‐ What?
‐ Oh, man.

01:23.208 --> 01:26.503
I have nothing planned for him,
not a Lownote‐themed treasure hunt

01:26.503 --> 01:29.464
or comprehensive slideshow
of his most cherished memories

01:29.464 --> 01:30.591
or anything!
‐ Hold on!

01:30.591 --> 01:33.468
How did you of all Trolls
forget a birthday?

01:33.468 --> 01:34.344
‐ I dunno.

01:34.344 --> 01:37.347
The Funk Calendar is very complicated.

01:37.347 --> 01:40.350
♪

01:40.350 --> 01:43.353
‐ Hey, according to this,
I'm 5,000 in Funk Years.

01:43.854 --> 01:44.855
That's fun.

01:45.856 --> 01:46.690
‐ Okay.

01:46.690 --> 01:47.983
Before the day ends,

01:47.983 --> 01:51.737
we are just gonna throw
an amazing surprise party for Lownote!

01:51.737 --> 01:54.072
And yes, I said "we," as in you and me.

01:54.072 --> 01:55.574
Welcome to friendship, Val!

01:55.574 --> 01:57.659
‐ But I had plans to‐‐
‐ Move, move, move!

01:57.659 --> 02:00.662
♪

02:04.291 --> 02:05.250
Woo!

02:05.250 --> 02:06.251
BOTH:
Yeah!

02:06.960 --> 02:08.545
‐ Woo, great job, Val!

02:08.545 --> 02:11.340
We made these invitations
at a record pace!

02:11.340 --> 02:13.383
‐ Yeah, but the party is today.

02:13.383 --> 02:15.802
How are we gonna to deliver
all these that fast?

02:15.802 --> 02:18.180
[ eagle screech ]

02:18.180 --> 02:22.517
‐ Y'know, if'n you aim to get them
invitations delivered fast,

02:22.517 --> 02:26.605
we Country Trolls have
a right reliable delivery service.

02:26.605 --> 02:30.609
A venerated institution
run by Trolls of integrity

02:30.609 --> 02:32.277
and fine repute.

02:33.403 --> 02:34.946
POPPY:
The Puffalo Express?

02:36.114 --> 02:37.616
Oh, you meant yourself.

02:37.949 --> 02:39.117
[ Gust laughing ]

02:39.618 --> 02:41.578
Gust, you really think you can get

02:41.578 --> 02:44.122
our invitations delivered
before party time?

02:44.456 --> 02:48.418
‐ Poppy, as a solemn carrier
in our sacred order,

02:48.418 --> 02:50.087
once I receive a parcel,

02:50.087 --> 02:52.881
I am sworn by the puffalo oath

02:52.881 --> 02:56.259
to deliver it to its destination on time,

02:56.843 --> 02:58.845
no matter what.

02:59.596 --> 03:01.390
‐ Really? Even in the rain?

03:01.890 --> 03:02.849
‐ Yes.

03:03.433 --> 03:04.267
‐ Heat?

03:04.559 --> 03:05.435
‐ Yes.

03:06.061 --> 03:07.187
‐ Gloom of night?

03:07.437 --> 03:10.607
‐ That's a weird way of saying it,
but yes.

03:11.358 --> 03:13.151
‐ Whoa!
‐ Whoa!

03:13.151 --> 03:16.279
‐ That's how it was
with my daddy before me

03:16.279 --> 03:18.490
and his mama before him.

03:18.490 --> 03:20.659
They never failed a delivery.

03:20.659 --> 03:25.080
And neither shall I on this day
if you're so inclined.

03:26.164 --> 03:29.709
‐ Yes, Gust, consider my cline all in.

03:29.709 --> 03:31.962
‐ Excellent! I'll assemble my team!

03:34.631 --> 03:36.091
‐ Woo‐hoo!

03:36.091 --> 03:39.886
We've got ourselves
a good ol' fashion mail deliverin' ya'll!

03:39.886 --> 03:41.054
[ Poppy and Val gasp ]

03:44.141 --> 03:45.142
‐ Hyah!

03:48.311 --> 03:49.438
‐ There they go.

03:49.646 --> 03:55.360
One invitation to Lownote's surprise party
for every single Troll in TrollsTopia.

03:55.569 --> 03:56.486
‐ Yep.

03:56.486 --> 03:59.281
Well, every Troll except Lownote, right?

03:59.656 --> 04:00.866
‐ Uh…

04:01.867 --> 04:06.872
One for Dante, one for Synth,
one for Lownote Jones…

04:08.498 --> 04:09.499
[ Poppy and Val gasp ]

04:09.499 --> 04:14.421
‐ We sent Lownote Jones
an invitation to his own surprise party?

04:14.421 --> 04:15.839
‐ We've got to catch Gust!

04:15.839 --> 04:16.756
VAL:
Wait!

04:18.091 --> 04:19.259
Don't go!

04:19.634 --> 04:20.510
‐ Hyah!

04:21.344 --> 04:23.096
‐ Puffalo Express, y'all!

04:23.096 --> 04:25.182
Heads up! Comin' atcha!

04:26.516 --> 04:28.685
‐ Yey!
‐ Yey!

04:29.269 --> 04:30.812
‐ Gust! Gust!
‐ Gust! Gust!

04:30.812 --> 04:32.147
‐ Whoa!

04:32.564 --> 04:33.857
‐ There's been a mistake.

04:33.857 --> 04:36.902
We accidentally sent
an invitation to Lownote Jones.

04:37.319 --> 04:40.697
‐ A surprise party invitation
to the surprised?

04:40.906 --> 04:44.409
My my, ain't that just a prickly pear
in your piñata.

04:44.868 --> 04:47.871
‐ Yes, there's really
no other way to describe it.

04:48.371 --> 04:50.749
So, I'll just grab it
from the Funk bag and‐‐

04:51.208 --> 04:52.000
BOTH:
Huh?

04:52.375 --> 04:55.712
‐ Poppy, I told you:
once I receive a parcel,

04:55.712 --> 05:01.009
I am sworn by the puffalo oath
to deliver it to its destination

05:01.593 --> 05:02.552
no matter‐‐

05:02.552 --> 05:03.386
‐ Ugh!

05:04.554 --> 05:06.223
Yes, you told us!

05:06.223 --> 05:09.351
It was very dramatic!
But can't you just make an exception?

05:09.559 --> 05:10.894
‐ No, I cannot.

05:11.144 --> 05:13.772
To do so would fail the legacy

05:13.772 --> 05:16.525
of all the Express Trolls
that came before me.

05:17.651 --> 05:18.777
Ladies.

05:20.111 --> 05:21.279
[ goat bleats ]

05:21.446 --> 05:24.199
‐ Great, the second Lownote
sees that invitation,

05:24.199 --> 05:25.575
his birthday is ruined.

05:25.909 --> 05:26.952
What do we do now?

05:27.244 --> 05:31.414
‐ The only thing we can do:
take that invitation back.

05:33.250 --> 05:34.835
‐ You chose a "bandit mask"

05:34.835 --> 05:37.587
that's color coordinated
with your outfit?

05:37.921 --> 05:38.922
‐ Yeah.

05:38.922 --> 05:41.424
And I have one for you too.

05:42.759 --> 05:43.635
‐ Oh!

05:44.386 --> 05:45.720
[ Val and Poppy growling ]

05:47.097 --> 05:47.931
[ goat bleats ]

05:49.349 --> 05:53.353
‐ See, Val, now wherever
Gust goes, we go.

05:53.603 --> 05:57.816
And the moment he lets his guard down,
that invitation is ours.

05:59.317 --> 06:00.318
‐ Hmm.

06:00.318 --> 06:02.612
Y'know, Gust, we'd make better time

06:02.612 --> 06:05.907
if we turn left here
through that field of tickle grass!

06:05.907 --> 06:07.242
BOTH:
Tickle grass?

06:07.617 --> 06:08.618
‐ Hyah!

06:10.912 --> 06:13.290
[ Poppy and Val try not to laugh ]

06:14.708 --> 06:18.211
‐ No, we should've cut right
through the tickle grass.

06:18.795 --> 06:19.796
BOTH:
What?

06:19.796 --> 06:20.964
GUST:
Hyah!

06:21.381 --> 06:23.466
[ Poppy and Val laughing ]

06:23.466 --> 06:25.927
‐ I am so frustrated right now!

06:26.928 --> 06:28.305
‐ I'm furious!

06:28.305 --> 06:30.307
[ Poppy and Val laughing ]

06:31.099 --> 06:33.476
Well, I didn't think it'd come to this.

06:33.810 --> 06:36.062
But we have to do
something extreme.

06:51.620 --> 06:52.704
[ Gust and Holly gasp ]

06:52.704 --> 06:54.289
‐ Woohoo!

06:54.289 --> 06:56.875
Those fireworks
are somethin' else!

06:57.042 --> 06:58.627
‐ They're so extreme!

06:59.336 --> 07:02.339
♪

07:06.843 --> 07:08.595
‐ You did it, Popsqueak.

07:08.845 --> 07:09.929
It's over.

07:10.263 --> 07:11.514
‐ Correction, Val:

07:11.514 --> 07:15.310
Once I tear this invitation up
so that Lownote never sees it,

07:15.310 --> 07:16.478
then it's over.

07:16.978 --> 07:17.812
Huh?

07:18.063 --> 07:20.732
"Dearest, Poppy,
apologies for the ruse,

07:20.732 --> 07:24.069
but this is a decoy invitation
to distract you

07:24.069 --> 07:25.820
whilst we finish our delivery.

07:25.820 --> 07:27.822
Hugspectfully yours, Gust."

07:28.031 --> 07:29.032
[ Poppy and Val gasp ]

07:30.700 --> 07:33.536
No, they're heading
to the Vibe Town Spaceship.

07:34.037 --> 07:35.038
BOTH:
Lownote!

07:35.497 --> 07:36.373
[ whistling ]

07:41.878 --> 07:43.046
Hyah!

07:43.380 --> 07:44.798
POPPY: Giddyap.
VAL: Hyah!

07:47.550 --> 07:48.718
‐ We got company.

07:48.968 --> 07:51.721
‐ Best lose 'em in the South Plains
of Country Corral.

07:51.721 --> 07:54.224
‐ The South Plains?
But that's where they're havin'

07:54.224 --> 07:56.142
the Glitter Dodgeball Tournament!

07:56.226 --> 07:57.394
‐ I know.

08:01.022 --> 08:03.400
‐ I'm callin' you out,
Haystack Wiggins!

08:03.400 --> 08:04.693
Make your move!

08:05.360 --> 08:06.736
‐ Thank ya kindly,

08:06.736 --> 08:10.573
but I respectfully insist
you make yer move first.

08:13.702 --> 08:14.869
GUST: H'yah!
‐ Ah!

08:14.869 --> 08:16.037
GUST:
Hyah! C'mon!

08:16.246 --> 08:17.080
‐ Ah!

08:17.455 --> 08:18.373
‐ Ah!

08:19.207 --> 08:20.125
‐ Oh!

08:20.125 --> 08:21.501
BOTH:
Oh!

08:23.712 --> 08:25.839
♪ Whoa ♪

08:26.506 --> 08:28.174
♪ Yeah! ♪

08:28.174 --> 08:29.008
‐ Hyah!

08:29.008 --> 08:30.218
♪ Ready or not ♪

08:30.218 --> 08:31.553
♪ Here I come ♪

08:31.553 --> 08:32.887
♪ You can't hide ♪

08:32.887 --> 08:34.431
♪ You can't run ♪

08:34.431 --> 08:38.727
♪ Cause I get what I want in this town ♪

08:38.727 --> 08:39.561
♪ Oh! ♪

08:39.561 --> 08:42.063
♪ Yeah, Imma ride into the storm ♪

08:42.230 --> 08:44.983
♪ No, I won't be backing out ♪

08:44.983 --> 08:49.946
♪ No pouring rain or hurricane
Ain't never gonna slow me down ♪

08:49.946 --> 08:51.489
♪ Said Imma ride into the storm ♪

08:51.489 --> 08:52.574
‐ I'm out!

08:52.824 --> 08:55.285
♪ I'll be coming in red hot ♪

08:55.410 --> 08:56.745
♪ Got a fire inside ♪

08:56.745 --> 08:58.246
♪ It's burnin' high ♪

08:58.246 --> 09:00.457
♪ And I won't ever stop ♪

09:00.457 --> 09:03.126
♪ Cause when the stakes are high
It's do or die ♪

09:03.126 --> 09:05.211
♪ And only one Troll ♪

09:05.211 --> 09:07.881
♪ Can come out on top ♪

09:08.381 --> 09:10.091
♪ Oh, oh ♪

09:10.300 --> 09:12.594
♪ Can come out on top ♪

09:13.428 --> 09:15.472
♪ And only one Troll ♪

09:15.472 --> 09:18.099
♪ Can come out on top! ♪♪

09:18.975 --> 09:23.104
‐ I'm sorry, Poppy.
But nothing can stop the Puffalo Express.

09:23.438 --> 09:24.522
‐ Maybe not.

09:24.647 --> 09:26.858
But I bet I can slow it down.

09:28.026 --> 09:29.319
‐ Tickle grass!

09:30.695 --> 09:33.823
[ Gust laughing ]

09:33.823 --> 09:35.992
It's… It's so dern tickly!

09:36.201 --> 09:38.203
[ Gust laughing ]

09:38.495 --> 09:39.370
‐ Got it!

09:39.871 --> 09:42.123
This party is still a surprise!

09:42.791 --> 09:43.708
GUST:
No!

09:44.626 --> 09:45.752
Please.

09:47.170 --> 09:49.172
‐ Sorry to give you
so much trouble, Gust,

09:49.172 --> 09:52.592
but it's really important
that the party not get spoiled.

09:53.343 --> 09:54.344
[ Gust sighing ]

09:54.844 --> 09:56.346
‐ I understand, Poppy.

09:56.805 --> 09:58.098
Well played.

09:59.808 --> 10:02.185
Still, I'm gonna have
to get used to the fact

10:02.185 --> 10:06.898
that I'm the first Puffalo Express Carrier
to not complete a job.

10:07.357 --> 10:09.734
The first to break the oath.

10:11.236 --> 10:13.029
‐ The first to break the oath?

10:18.076 --> 10:20.203
Actually, Gust, here.

10:21.871 --> 10:22.705
‐ Wha‐‐?

10:22.831 --> 10:23.998
You mean?

10:23.998 --> 10:27.377
‐ Yeah, making a big deal
out of Lownote's birthday

10:27.377 --> 10:29.629
is really important to me,

10:30.004 --> 10:32.215
but I'll get another chance
next year.

10:32.549 --> 10:35.301
What matters more is
that you finish this delivery…

10:35.885 --> 10:37.011
no matter what.

10:37.220 --> 10:40.056
♪

10:40.306 --> 10:41.307
‐ Poppy…

10:43.226 --> 10:44.727
I thank you

10:44.727 --> 10:48.106
and The legacy of the Puffalo Express
thanks you.

10:52.277 --> 10:53.778
Puffalo Express!

10:59.033 --> 11:00.034
[ Val and Poppy gasp ]

11:00.410 --> 11:01.786
Of course…

11:02.620 --> 11:04.956
now that my duty is fulfilled,

11:04.956 --> 11:07.876
I am no longer
Gust the mail carrier.

11:08.918 --> 11:09.752
‐ Huh?

11:10.920 --> 11:12.672
‐ I'm just Gust your friend,

11:13.089 --> 11:16.843
which means I can help you
get that invitation back

11:16.843 --> 11:18.261
before Lownote reads it!

11:19.095 --> 11:21.598
‐ Wait, Gust, what are you saying?

11:21.764 --> 11:25.727
‐ I'm sayin'
we take that invitation back.

11:28.062 --> 11:29.272
[ Gust and Holly growl ]

11:29.564 --> 11:30.565
[ Val and Poppy gasp ]

11:31.149 --> 11:32.317
[ Val and Poppy growl ]

11:32.483 --> 11:35.486
♪

11:35.486 --> 11:38.156
EVERYONE:
Yeeehaw!

11:42.827 --> 11:45.622
[ Poppy humming ]

11:46.164 --> 11:47.165
VAL:
Uh…

11:47.165 --> 11:49.500
What's with all the decorations,
Pop‐squeak?

11:50.126 --> 11:53.796
‐ I'm glad you asked, Val.
And I am all too happy to tell you.

11:54.380 --> 11:55.590
I have no idea!

11:56.299 --> 11:58.426
‐ You don't know
why you're decorating?

11:58.635 --> 12:01.763
‐ Nope!
I just found this box and well,

12:01.763 --> 12:05.475
I'm not gonna let a bunch of decorations
just sit here, am I?

12:05.475 --> 12:07.560
[ Poppy laughs ]

12:08.478 --> 12:10.104
‐ Wonder who left these here?

12:10.188 --> 12:12.357
CLOUD GUY:
It was…

12:13.858 --> 12:17.445
No, no, you had it right before. Me.
EVERYONE: Ah!

12:18.529 --> 12:19.948
‐ Nice to see you,

12:20.156 --> 12:23.618
Poppy, Troll I sometimes bother,
Troll I'm scared of.

12:23.618 --> 12:24.869
BOTH:
Cloud Guy!

12:24.869 --> 12:25.703
‐ By the by,

12:26.537 --> 12:30.333
those decorations are for a little holiday
we clouds call "Cloudmas."

12:30.333 --> 12:31.167
[ Poppy gasps ]

12:31.167 --> 12:32.502
‐ A new holiday?

12:32.502 --> 12:33.962
Tell me everything!

12:33.962 --> 12:35.588
Do you wear Cloudmas sweaters?

12:36.005 --> 12:37.924
‐ Does this answer your question?

12:38.341 --> 12:39.676
‐ Oh, we wear sweaters.

12:40.468 --> 12:41.344
‐ Yes!

12:41.928 --> 12:43.596
‐ Cloudmas is the best!

12:43.596 --> 12:45.348
The gifts, the games,

12:45.348 --> 12:47.684
the fluffy desserts
my Cloud momma makes,

12:47.684 --> 12:50.603
but most of all,
it's that special time of year

12:50.603 --> 12:53.982
when clouds show kindness
to the ones they care about most.

12:54.190 --> 12:57.527
And for me,
that someone is Branch.

12:59.028 --> 12:59.904
‐ Branch?

12:59.904 --> 13:02.240
‐ But you pester him like,
all the time.

13:02.407 --> 13:05.660
‐ Exactly! Do you realize
how much joy that gives me?

13:05.910 --> 13:07.745
Filling his bed with live fish,

13:07.745 --> 13:09.914
replacing his toothpaste
with mayonnaise.

13:10.081 --> 13:13.126
Oh, and then there's
the 'ol "Frosty Trousers"

13:13.126 --> 13:16.504
where I take a bucket of ice,
wait 'til his back is turned and‐‐

13:17.714 --> 13:19.716
No! No tricks this time!

13:19.716 --> 13:21.676
I've got to do something
to show Branch

13:21.676 --> 13:24.387
what he means to me
before Cloudmas slips away,

13:25.388 --> 13:26.723
but I don't know how.

13:27.056 --> 13:28.141
BOTH:
Aww.

13:28.391 --> 13:30.393
‐ The only thing I'm good at
is pranking

13:31.978 --> 13:35.064
and having abs so defined
they can grate cheese.

13:37.025 --> 13:37.942
BOTH:
Aww.

13:38.443 --> 13:40.069
‐ Don't you worry, Cloud Guy.

13:40.069 --> 13:44.782
We are gonna drop everything to help you
do something kind for Branch this instant.

13:44.782 --> 13:45.867
Right, girls?

13:45.867 --> 13:46.743
‐ Right!

13:47.118 --> 13:47.952
‐ Really?

13:49.579 --> 13:51.205
POPPY:
Uh, yeah…

13:52.040 --> 13:52.915
We'll, um…

13:52.915 --> 13:55.918
We'll just drop everything sure.

13:57.003 --> 13:58.379
‐ Poppy, it's fine.

13:58.379 --> 14:00.882
You can finish putting up
the decorations first.

14:01.215 --> 14:02.258
‐ Thank you!

14:02.258 --> 14:03.342
[ laughing ]

14:03.342 --> 14:04.260
Yes!

14:04.260 --> 14:05.553
[ laughing ]

14:06.429 --> 14:08.931
If you really wanna do
something nice for Branch,

14:08.931 --> 14:10.933
there are lots of options.

14:10.933 --> 14:14.062
‐ Let's start with a little role playing.
Pretend I'm Branch‐‐

14:14.062 --> 14:14.896
CLOUD GUY:
Heh!

14:15.688 --> 14:20.109
Oh! Val, I'm so sorry.
My instincts just kicked in.

14:20.109 --> 14:21.986
I swear, it won't happen again.

14:23.404 --> 14:24.238
Heh!

14:24.238 --> 14:25.448
EVERYBODY:
Cloud Guy!

14:26.157 --> 14:27.825
‐ Gah! I can't stop!

14:28.826 --> 14:30.078
Run, Val, run!

14:30.078 --> 14:33.581
[ Val screaming ]

14:33.790 --> 14:36.584
[ Cloud Guy weeping ]

14:37.085 --> 14:40.880
‐ A simple, considerate gift basket
can brighten anyone's day!

14:41.464 --> 14:42.423
Hmm…

14:42.423 --> 14:44.258
Scented candles, check.

14:44.550 --> 14:46.260
Flavorberry muffins, check.

14:46.636 --> 14:49.055
Some of Branch's favorite cologne?

14:49.222 --> 14:52.975
‐ It's called Cantankerous
Underdweller for Men.

14:55.311 --> 14:57.522
‐ Oh, bonus points for that.

14:57.522 --> 14:58.356
‐ Yes.

14:58.356 --> 15:03.694
‐ Now, just one final box to check here,
"Basket does not explode"?

15:04.195 --> 15:05.279
‐ Hmm.

15:05.279 --> 15:06.697
Mmhmm, mmhmm.

15:06.697 --> 15:09.325
In that case,
you might want to hit the dirt.

15:10.201 --> 15:11.369
[ everybody screaming]

15:12.870 --> 15:13.788
POPPY:
Cloud Guy,

15:13.788 --> 15:16.707
why don't you just write Branch
a heartfelt note?

15:17.500 --> 15:19.001
‐ Uh, I dunno.

15:19.001 --> 15:20.628
Where would I even start?

15:21.337 --> 15:22.296
Except…

15:23.506 --> 15:24.423
Hmm.

15:27.927 --> 15:29.178
Uh‐huh, uh‐huh.

15:30.805 --> 15:32.473
Oh, that's good.

15:33.516 --> 15:34.976
And…

15:35.685 --> 15:36.519
Done!

15:37.854 --> 15:38.855
‐ Oh!
‐ No.

15:40.314 --> 15:42.316
[ Cloud Guy crying ]

15:42.483 --> 15:44.694
‐ See, I can't help myself!

15:44.902 --> 15:47.363
This Cloudmas is a disaster!

15:47.363 --> 15:49.740
[ Cloud Guy crying ]

15:51.868 --> 15:54.537
‐ It's okay, Cloud Guy,
we'll help you figure it out.

15:55.746 --> 15:56.747
‐ Really?

15:56.914 --> 15:57.748
‐ Really.

15:57.915 --> 16:01.794
Try again, but just focus
on telling Branch how you feel.

16:02.712 --> 16:04.213
‐ Oh, okay.

16:04.213 --> 16:07.216
♪

16:09.677 --> 16:11.304
‐ All right, good.

16:11.304 --> 16:15.516
Except this part where you wrote,
"Your smile can light up a room.

16:15.516 --> 16:18.895
And your face perfectly matches
the circumference of a pie?"

16:18.895 --> 16:19.729
‐ Uh‐huh?

16:19.729 --> 16:21.606
‐ Just go with the smile part.

16:21.606 --> 16:23.774
‐ Hmm… Okay, good note.

16:23.774 --> 16:26.777
♪

16:29.030 --> 16:32.450
‐ This part about the bond you share
lasting through the ages?

16:32.450 --> 16:33.910
Write more about that.

16:34.118 --> 16:37.121
And lose this part where you list
all the kinds of fish

16:37.121 --> 16:38.206
you've put in his bed.

16:38.206 --> 16:39.749
‐ Oh!

16:39.749 --> 16:42.710
♪

16:42.835 --> 16:45.087
‐ You misspelled Frosty Trousers.

16:45.254 --> 16:46.255
‐ Mmhmm!

16:46.255 --> 16:48.382
‐ Also, don't write Frosty Trousers.

16:48.674 --> 16:50.176
‐ Hmm!

16:52.887 --> 16:53.721
Well?

16:54.847 --> 16:55.681
‐ It's‐‐

16:56.432 --> 16:58.601
It's just beautiful, Cloud Guy.

16:58.893 --> 17:01.938
‐ I woo‐hoo'd, I boo‐hoo'd.

17:02.146 --> 17:03.272
[ Holly sniffs ]

17:03.814 --> 17:04.815
[ Val sniffs ]

17:05.149 --> 17:06.651
‐ Whatever, it's fine.

17:08.236 --> 17:09.403
Stop looking at me!

17:09.403 --> 17:10.905
[ Val sobs ]

17:11.239 --> 17:13.115
[ Branch whistling ]

17:13.491 --> 17:14.909
‐ Okay, final step.

17:15.076 --> 17:19.247
Hmm, we give you one minute
before your impish nature kicks in.

17:19.247 --> 17:21.332
‐ So, get over there,
give Branch the note

17:21.332 --> 17:24.293
and get out before you ruin
this thoughtful Cloudmas gesture

17:24.293 --> 17:25.378
by bein'…

17:25.795 --> 17:28.256
well, by bein' you.

17:29.257 --> 17:30.591
CLOUD GUY:
Uh, Branch…?

17:31.425 --> 17:33.594
‐ Cloud Guy!
What are you doing?

17:33.594 --> 17:35.972
Oh! Are you trying to give me
frosty trousers?

17:36.430 --> 17:37.473
‐ No, no, Branch.

17:37.473 --> 17:40.059
Today's a special cloud holiday
called Cloudmas.

17:40.059 --> 17:42.812
And I just wanted to give you this.

17:46.023 --> 17:48.818
‐ Oh, you wanna tell me
how you feel, huh?

17:49.110 --> 17:50.778
Ha, this should be good.

17:50.778 --> 17:53.781
♪

17:55.950 --> 17:59.161
Huh, actually this part
is kind of nice.

18:00.037 --> 18:01.289
‐ Oh!

18:01.539 --> 18:03.541
‐ "Smile lights up a room"?

18:04.333 --> 18:05.251
Huh.

18:07.169 --> 18:08.170
Oh, wow.

18:08.921 --> 18:12.008
Yeah, I've felt that before,
I just didn't know how to say it.

18:12.508 --> 18:14.510
You… You really mean all this?

18:15.303 --> 18:16.345
‐ Mmhmm!

18:19.932 --> 18:20.975
‐ Thanks, buddy.

18:23.853 --> 18:25.187
EVERYBODY:
Aww!

18:26.063 --> 18:29.233
‐ Well, Merry Cloudmas, Branch.

18:31.819 --> 18:34.530
‐ Hey, uh, Cloud Guy,
wait a second.

18:35.239 --> 18:38.409
‐ Whoa, no, no. Don't stop,
your one minute's almost up!

18:38.659 --> 18:41.078
‐ Why don't you come inside
and stay for a bit?

18:41.329 --> 18:42.371
We can catch up!

18:42.538 --> 18:43.664
‐ Stay?

18:45.750 --> 18:49.670
Uh, Branch, ha‐ha, I'd love to,
but I'm booked.

18:49.879 --> 18:53.716
Gotta wash my socks,
then I… I gotta dry my socks.

18:54.050 --> 18:55.176
‐ Your socks?

18:55.468 --> 18:57.553
But you just said
all those nice things…

18:58.179 --> 19:00.139
unless you didn't really mean it.

19:00.348 --> 19:01.849
‐ No, no! I did! I just‐‐

19:02.975 --> 19:03.851
I'd…

19:05.186 --> 19:06.187
I…

19:06.187 --> 19:08.064
I would love
to come inside, Branch.

19:08.522 --> 19:10.107
‐ Oh, okay, great!

19:11.067 --> 19:13.277
‐ Oh, no, no, no!
Not down in the bunker!

19:15.071 --> 19:16.697
‐ Help me.

19:19.450 --> 19:22.953
‐ Can I offer you a refreshment?
Perhaps something that's been sitting

19:22.953 --> 19:25.706
in a mason jar
for the last 120 to 130 months?

19:26.457 --> 19:28.042
‐ Uh, sure.

19:28.042 --> 19:28.918
Ha‐ha.

19:29.377 --> 19:30.586
‐ Terrific.

19:30.586 --> 19:32.755
Just hold this heaping
bucket of ice one sec

19:32.755 --> 19:34.757
while I turn around and pour.

19:35.758 --> 19:38.260
‐ Heaping b‐bucket of ice?

19:39.095 --> 19:41.764
[ Branch whistling ]

19:43.599 --> 19:45.768
Huh…

19:46.686 --> 19:48.604
[ Cloud Guy growling ]

19:50.481 --> 19:51.399
BRANCH:
Okay!

19:52.316 --> 19:53.275
[ Cloud Guy gasps ]

19:54.235 --> 19:56.654
‐ Huh…

19:57.655 --> 19:59.990
‐ Now to add the ice, and…

20:00.658 --> 20:01.659
Huh…

20:02.243 --> 20:03.494
[ Cloud Guy shivering ]

20:03.744 --> 20:04.578
[ timer rings ]

20:04.578 --> 20:06.497
Oh! My pie is ready!

20:07.498 --> 20:08.416
‐ Wait!

20:08.582 --> 20:10.918
You made a pie?

20:11.585 --> 20:13.087
‐ Oh, no, no…

20:13.963 --> 20:15.548
I made lots of pies!

20:18.134 --> 20:20.136
Yeah, I've actually been baking all day.

20:20.428 --> 20:23.305
Y'see, I got up early
to try to find some stuff

20:23.305 --> 20:25.641
and forks in my yard
for some berries,

20:25.641 --> 20:28.060
but it turns out the berries
where on the other…

20:28.060 --> 20:29.895
CLOUD GUY:
C'mon fight it, Cloud Guy!

20:29.895 --> 20:33.524
If you give in and throw one of these pies
at Branch, you'll ruin Cloudmas!

20:37.695 --> 20:40.698
♪

20:42.450 --> 20:43.367
Oh…

20:45.035 --> 20:46.328
Oh, oh, huh, uh…

20:47.455 --> 20:48.289
‐ Here.

20:48.873 --> 20:49.832
‐ Huh?

20:50.374 --> 20:51.709
I‐is that…?

20:51.709 --> 20:55.755
‐ A traditional Cloudmas Pie!
At least, I think so.

20:55.755 --> 20:57.840
I had to bake a lot
of trial‐and‐error pies,

20:57.840 --> 20:59.675
but I think I finally got it right.

21:02.303 --> 21:05.306
♪

21:05.306 --> 21:06.474
[ Cloud Guy gasps ]

21:06.474 --> 21:09.018
[ child's laughter ]

21:11.103 --> 21:13.898
‐ It's just like my Cloud Momma
used to make.

21:14.482 --> 21:17.693
‐ Yeah, well, I came across
this old library book

21:17.693 --> 21:20.905
about Cloudmas a while back
and, I dunno,

21:20.905 --> 21:23.324
I guess I wanted to do
something nice for you too.

21:23.741 --> 21:26.410
‐ You really did all this for me?

21:27.161 --> 21:29.413
‐ Does this answer your question?

21:29.580 --> 21:30.706
‐ I did it for you!

21:31.207 --> 21:33.042
[ both laughing ]

21:33.042 --> 21:35.336
♪ Decorate the cloud ♪

21:35.336 --> 21:37.797
♪ Smiles all around ♪

21:37.880 --> 21:42.551
♪ It's the perfect Cloudmas
Kinda weather ♪

21:42.551 --> 21:45.054
♪ Silver linings shine ♪

21:45.054 --> 21:47.389
♪ Lighting up the sky ♪

21:47.389 --> 21:52.645
♪ When we're spending
Cloudmas time together ♪

21:52.645 --> 21:57.441
♪ Cuz it's the season where
A friendship starts to bloom ♪

21:57.441 --> 22:01.737
♪ If anything can bring
Together me and you ♪

22:01.737 --> 22:07.743
♪ You know it's spending
Cloudmas time together ♪♪

22:09.703 --> 22:10.538
‐ Wow.

22:10.871 --> 22:12.623
What a day we've had.

22:13.791 --> 22:16.252
‐ What‐a‐day.

22:17.837 --> 22:18.921
BOTH:
I hate this.

22:20.589 --> 22:23.676
‐ Branch, I had an amazing Cloudmas
with you, but‐‐

22:23.676 --> 22:25.427
‐ It's just not who we are.

22:26.220 --> 22:27.221
BOTH:
Huh?

22:27.221 --> 22:29.390
‐ It's midnight! Which means…

22:30.057 --> 22:31.600
BOTH:
Cloudmas is over!

22:31.767 --> 22:37.273
♪ Spending Cloudmas time together ♪♪

22:38.315 --> 22:41.110
♪ Yeah, Imma ride into the storm ♪

22:41.110 --> 22:43.821
♪ No, I won't be backing out ♪

22:43.821 --> 22:46.240
♪ No pouring rain or hurricane ♪

22:46.240 --> 22:48.951
♪ Ain't never gonna slow me down ♪

22:48.951 --> 22:51.662
♪ Said Imma ride into the storm ♪

22:51.662 --> 22:54.290
♪ I'll be coming in red hot ♪

22:54.290 --> 22:55.666
♪ Got a fire inside ♪

22:55.666 --> 22:56.959
♪ It's burnin' high ♪

22:56.959 --> 22:59.295
♪ And I won't ever stop ♪

22:59.295 --> 23:02.089
♪ Cause when the stakes are high
It's do or die ♪

23:02.089 --> 23:03.966
♪ And only one Troll ♪

23:03.966 --> 23:06.552
♪ Can come out on top ♪♪
